column1: Time Zone is Central European (Winter) Time, or UTC +1. In winter, this is equal to the local time.
The UFP data were filtered based on instrument error codes and hourly averaged pulse height (> 2000 mV), with some manual adjustments around maintenance times.

The data in the last column are adjusted towards a common scale (the EPC3783 operated by GGD-Amsterdam at Ookmeer), based on regression coefficients obtained during a comparison effort at Ookmeer station in the summer of 2022.
Due to the needs of our software developers and technical difficulties, the instrument at this site was reinstalled later (January 2023) than at the other sites (autumn 2022).
The EPC was removed form this station on 3 May 2023 to be used in a different field experiment.

column8: Checked UFP concentrations adjusted with Ookmeer regressions [#/cm3]
